('Facebook Updating Their Terms of Service to Better Explain How Facebook Works', 31, '', 'TECHNOLOGY', 'ENGLISH', 'fb.jpg', '', 'Anna Benckert, VP and Associate General Counsel posted that Facebook is updating their term of service to make people clear about how online services work and use of personal information. \r\n\r\n', '2019-07-07 00:01:19', 'Technology,Trending', 'They want people to understand how Facebook makes money and the rights which people have when using their services. The updates do not change any of our commitments or policies â€”they solely explain things more clearly.', 'He also states that they are giving more transparency and control to the people over their information. As the facebook introduced updates to " why am I seeing this ad ?" and "why I am seeing this post ?" to help people understand and control what they see in the news feed\r\n', ' Facebook includes more details on how they make money, including a new introduction explaining that we donâ€™t charge money from the users to use their products because businesses and organizations pay them to show ads to the users.', 'Facebook also clarify that when people share their own content like photos and videos. They continue to own the intellectual property rights in that content.  It also grants Facebook to do things like a display that content and that permission ends when the content is deleted from Facebook. ', 'when you delete content youâ€™ve shared. For example, when you delete something youâ€™ve posted, itâ€™s no longer visible but it can take up to 90 days to be removed from their systems.', 'The updated terms will take effect for everyone on Facebook around the world on July 31, 2019, and users can preview the changes by visiting their Terms of Service page.', '', '', '', 'NO', 600062, 'chennai'),
(' Facebook is making an update to improve comment ranking on public posts ', 32, '', 'TECHNOLOGY', 'ENGLISH', 'f.jpg', '', ' Facebook is making an update to improve comment ranking on public posts, and how this works and how Pages and people can control their own comment ranking settings.\r\nin addition to ranking posts in  News Feed, Facebook ranks comments on public posts from Pages and people with a lot of followers, since these posts tend to have many comments. In order to show people relevant and quality comments, they incorporate a number of signals, including:', '2019-07-07 00:01:19', 'Technology,Trending', 'Integrity signals: \r\nin this signal facebook want people to see safe and authentic comments. If a comment violates their Community Standards, they remove it. they also take into account other signals, like engagement-bait, to address the integrity of information and improve the quality of comments people see.', 'Facebook is using more surveys to help them to understand the types of comments people want to see, so they can rank those higher. This includes signals including whether people like, react to, or reply to a comment.', 'People can moderate the comments on their post by hiding, deleting, or engaging with comments. The ranking is on by default for Pages and people with a lot of followers, but Pages and people with a lot of followers can choose to turn off comment ranking. People who donâ€™t have as many followers will not have comment ranking turned on automatically since there are fewer comments overall, but any person can decide to enable comment ranking by going to their settings. ', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'NO', 0, ''),
('Android pie come with AI technology for smarter and  simpler experience', 33, '', 'TECHNOLOGY', 'ENGLISH', 'pie.jpg', '', 'The latest release of Android is here! And it comes with a heaping helping of artificial intelligence baked in to make your phone smarter, simpler and more tailored to you. \r\n Android 9  built to learn from the users and work better for the more they use it. From predicting users next task so that they jump right into the action they want to take,\r\n to prioritizing battery power for the apps they use most, to helping you disconnect from users phone at the end of the day.', '2019-07-07 18:33:36', 'Technology,Trending', 'Android 9 aims to make users phone even smarter by learning from them and adapting to their usage patterns. Thatâ€™s why Android 9 comes with features like Adaptive Battery, which learns the users of the app use most and prioritizes battery for them, and Adaptive Brightness, which learns how users like to set the brightness in different settings.', 'Android 9 also helps users to get things done faster with App Actions, which predicts what users want to do next based on their context and displays that action right on their phone.  for example Say itâ€™s Tuesday morning and youâ€™re preparing for your commute: youâ€™ll be suggested actions like navigating to work on Google Maps or resuming an audiobook with Google Play Books. And when you put in headphones after work, you may see options to call your mom or start your favorite playlist.', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'NO', 0, 'banglore'),
('Why javascript is the best language in the world. and why you should learn it', 34, '', 'TECHNOLOGY', 'ENGLISH', 'js.png', '', 'There is no doubt that javascript is one of the leading languages in the industry. And also the most loved language in the world.and is still increasing in popularity.\r\n According to t Stack Overflow, JavaScript is the most commonly used programming language, for the sixth year in a row. The popularity of JavaScript rose from 57% in 2013 to 70% in 2017. ', '2019-07-07 22:30:00', 'Technology', 'JavaScript is used for frontend development and. Itâ€™s easy to get started with and to adapt easily. It is a scripting language and doesn''t need any compilation and installation of tools.', ' you can build interactive projects during the learning process .you can write code that will run into your browser and also  u can easily interact with its UI', 'JavaScript has the largest and most active repository of library code in the world. People in the JavaScript community are very active and supportive in sharing and making use of each other''s code â€“ JavaScript has a large community on StackOverflow and over 3,600 JavaScript Meetup groups worldwide. Beginners, and you can share your code too!', 'we can use javascript in different fields like Client-side validation, Dynamic drop-down menus Displaying date and time Validate user input in an HTML form before sending the data to a server. Build forms that respond to user input without accessing a server. Change the appearance of HTML documents and dynamically write HTML into separate Windows. Open and close new windows or frames. Manipulate HTML "layers" including hiding, moving, and allowing the user to drag them around a browser window. Build small but complete client-side programs. Displaying pop-up windows and dialog boxes (like an alert dialog box, confirm dialog box and prompt dialog box)', '', '', '', '', '', 'NO', 0, 'banglore'),
