('Wipro recognised as "2018  citrix cloud partner of the year" for Asia Pacific & Japan region', 51, '', 'CORPORATE', 'HINDI', 'Wiprorertxflx.jpg', '', '<p>as we know <strong>Wipro</strong> is a leading global information technology, consulting and business process services company. &nbsp;Provides Service in the power of cognitive computing, hyper-automation, robotics, cloud, analytics and emerging technologies to help clients, adapt to the digital world and make them successful. The company has over 170,000 dedicated employees serving clients across six continents. today They announced that the company has been recognized with the &lsquo;2018 Citrix Cloud Partner of the Year&rsquo; award for India and the Asia Pacific &amp; Japan (APJ) region. Wipro received the award for its exemplary contribution towards enabling customers to determine their cloud journey in the area of the digitalization</p>', '2019-07-09 22:12:00', '', '<p><strong>Wipro </strong>was recognized by<strong>&nbsp;Citrix</strong> from among 80 global service providers offering cloud-enabled infrastructure services in the Asia Pacific &amp; Japan region for its contribution to revenue, strategic client wins, sales engagement and investments in modern tools and cloud technologies, to help clients accelerate their digital journey. </p>', '<p><strong>Paul Fecteau, Acting Partner AVP for Asia Pacific &amp; Japan, and Managing Director of World-Wide Partner Programs and Operations, Citrix&nbsp;</strong>said,<strong>&nbsp;</strong>&ldquo;Wipro has demonstrated outstanding innovation, achievement, and alignment with both our vision and the growing needs of our mutual clients. Their success in creating a deal pipeline, closing business, and helping customers accelerate their journey to the cloud is why we are privileged to recognize Wipro as our 2018 Cloud Partner of the Year for both India and the APJ regions.&rdquo; </p>', '<p><strong>source: </strong><em><u>Wipro news Room</u></em></p>', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'NO', 0, 'Banglore'),
('Wipro Launches Pivotal Software centre of excellence in dallas texas', 52, '', 'CORPORATE', 'ENGLISH', 'OpenOffice-Wipro-Adkison-4.jpg', '', '<p tabindex="0"><strong>Wipro Limited</strong> India&#39;s leading global information technology, consulting and business process services company, and Pivotal Software, Inc. a leading cloud-native platform provider, announced today the official opening of the Pivotal Center of Excellence at Wipro&rsquo;s Dallas office, to accelerate the innovation and digital transformation capabilities offered to joint customers. Wipro will expand its Dallas footprint and hire locally to help deliver these capabilities and other innovations. In addition, Wipro will expand the design services it offers clients by opening a new Design studio in Dallas..</p>', '2019-07-10 22:17:46', 'Buisness', '<p tabindex="0">The Pivotal Center of Excellence in Dallas will serve as a co-creation lab for both Wipro and Pivotal to build new solutions with their joint customers as well as demonstrate examples of digital transformation outcomes they have achieved with clients. Wipro&rsquo;s Pivotal relationship is operated through its digital transformation arm Wipro Digital and includes an existing Center of Excellence in Bangalore, India. Wipro Digital team members are building and transforming cloud-native applications for clients as well as transforming the way that clients build software with the Pivotal platform. &nbsp;</p><p tabindex="0"><br></p>', '<p tabindex="0">Wipro joined Pivotal&rsquo;s partner program in 2017, and in 2018 the two companies built a strategic partnership together. By March 2020, Wipro Digital will have over 2,000 knowledge workers trained to build and support Pivotal solutions. &nbsp;Additional Centers of Excellence are planned around the world as well.</p>', '<p>Read more: <strong>Wipro news room</strong></p>', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'NO', 0, 'Dallas'),
('Know the recruitment Procedure of Facebook', 53, '', 'CORPORATE', 'ENGLISH', 'fb3.jpg', '', '<p>Getting a job at Facebook is the dream of every student. Who doesn&#39;t want to get hired from facebook especially in technical fields? The interview process isn&rsquo;t exactly the same for every role or team but in general, it follows somewhat of a pattern. But it also varies from a technical and a non-technical. for the technical field, You have to go through different screening and interviews.</p><p><br></p>', '2019-07-10 22:34:25', 'Buisness', '<p>You&rsquo;ll likely talk to a recruiter first if it&#39;s not a campus drive. According to your background and experience and if it makes a good fit for their teams then they will recruit You.</p>', '<p>In some cases, a recruiter might introduce you to another recruiter who hires for a team that is a better fit.</p>', '<p>you need to do 1&ndash;2 technical phone screens as the next step. Depending on your area of expertise, team, and level of experience, this could be everything from coding to Linux troubleshooting. If you&rsquo;re in management, you might do a combination of management/tech interviews before as your phone screens.</p>', '<p>if You will pass the screening test then they will call you to come onsite. During your onsite, You have to pass 4-6 interviews on average. Most of these will be technical and specific to the organization or team you&rsquo;re interviewing for. Nearly all onsite interviews will include some variation of code and system design plus soft skills or team fit interview.</p>', '<p>Then they will review Your feedback and make a decision! Offer or No Offer</p>', '', '', '', '', 'NO', 0, 'banglore'),
('TOP COMPANIES OWNED BY FACEBOOK', 54, 'ADMIN', 'CORPORATE', 'ENGLISH', 'mark.jpg', '', '<p><strong>1: INSTAGRAM</strong>.</p><p>&nbsp;Instagram helped Facebook to shift its user base from the original web browser service to an app-based service, an overall number of the Instagram app users have been increased over the years. Facebook purchased Instagram for $1 billion on April 9, 2012, Instagram is one of the leading social media platforms in the world and is been estimated to be worth $100 billion. Instagram generated money through platform advertisements. some analysists indicate that Instagram generates more advertising revenue than Facebook, billion or more in revenue per year.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><br></p>', '2019-07-10 23:54:07', 'Buisness', '<p><strong>2: WHATSAPP</strong></p><p>WhatsApp is a messaging and calling service available throughout the world. &nbsp;WhatsApp was Founded in 2009. Facebook acquired WhatsApp for a reported $19 billion on February 19, 2014.WhatsApp allows users to message and call other users of the app for no cost, regardless of location around the globe. As of February of 2018, WhatsApp had surpassed Instagram&#39;s user base, with about 1.5 billion active users. WhatsApp generated revenue only through its initial purchase price of $1 But in some location its service is free.&nbsp;</p>', '<p><strong>3: Oculus VR</strong></p><p>Facebook acquired Oculus VR on March 25, 2014, for a reported $2.3 billion. Founded in 2012, Oculus VR is a technology company and one of the leaders in the emerging virtual reality technology space. The company is best known for Oculus Rift, it&#39;s virtual reality headset hardware that was designed for video gaming. Although Facebook has not revealed a revenue breakdown for Oculus, it seems clear that the company is interested in capitalizing on this purchase in an attempt to dominate the virtual reality software and hardware market.</p><p><br></p>', '<p><strong>4: FRIENDFEED</strong></p><p>Facebook bought FriendFeed by $47.5 million in 10, 2009.FriendFeed was one of the first companies that Facebook purchased, but its service was shut down in April 2015.</p>', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'NO', 0, 'Paolo alto'),
