(20, 'In Latest Upgrade Instagram is using  artificial intelligence to detect bullying and  harmful content in comments, photos and videos. ', 'TECHNOLOGY', 'ENGLISH', 'insta.jpg', '<p><strong>Instagram&nbsp;</strong>has announced a new feature to prevent online bullying and harmful content. The tools used by Instagram helps in a deep understanding of how people bully each other and how they respond to bullying on Instagram.&nbsp;</p>', 'Restrict_En_3-1 (2).png', '<p>Online bullying is a complex issue. For years and now Instagram has used artificial intelligence to detect bullying and other types of harmful content in <a href="https://instagram-press.com/blog/2017/06/29/keeping-instagram-a-safe-place-for-self-expression/">comments</a>, <a href="https://instagram-press.com/blog/2018/05/01/protecting-our-community-from-bullying-comments-2/">photos, and videos</a>. These help teens who are less likely to report online bullying even when they are the ones who experience it the most.  </p>', 'Restrict_En_3-1.png', '<p>This intervention gives people a chance to reflect and undo their comment and prevents the recipient from receiving a harmful comment notification.</p>', 'Technology', '2019-08-09 18:14:00', '', 0, 0, '<p>.</p><p>this new feature allows people to control their Instagram experience, without notifying someone who may be targeting them. Soon, Instagram will begin testing<span style="background-color: transparent;">&nbsp;a new way to protect users account from unwanted interactions called Restrict. Once users Restrict someone, comments on their posts from that person will only be visible to that person. users can choose to make a restricted person&rsquo;s comments visible to others by approving their comments. Restricted people won&rsquo;t be able to see when you&rsquo;re active on Instagram or when you&rsquo;ve read their direct messages.&nbsp;</span></p><p><br></p>', '', '', '', '', '', '', 0, 'Paolo Alto', 'NO'),
(21, 'Top 3 highest paying technical job in usa', 'CORPORATE', 'ENGLISH', 'programming.jpeg', '<p><strong>Computer Programmer</strong></p><p><strong>Entry Level Salary:&nbsp;</strong>$45,000 &amp; up<br><strong>Median Salary:&nbsp;</strong>$81,530<br><strong>Top 10% Earn:&nbsp;</strong>$132,800</p><p><br></p>', 'Web-development-designing-Anvar-Freelancer-1.png', '<p><strong>Web Developer</strong></p><p><strong>Entry Level Salary:&nbsp;</strong>$36,770 &amp; up<br><strong>Median Salary:&nbsp;</strong>$66,970<br><strong>Top 10% Earn:&nbsp;</strong>$118,620</p>', 'computer-support-specialists-720x340.jpg', '<p><strong>Computer Support Specialist</strong></p><p><strong>Entry Level Salary:&nbsp;</strong>$28,990 &amp; up<br><strong>Median Salary:&nbsp;</strong>$51,400<br><strong>Top 10% Earn:&nbsp;</strong>$81,650</p>', 'Buisness', '2019-07-10 23:09:41', '', 0, 0, '<p><strong>Computer &amp; Information Systems Manager</strong><br><strong>Entry Level Salary:&nbsp;</strong>$58,990 &amp; up<br><strong>Median Salary:</strong>&nbsp;$131,600</p>', '', '', '', '', '', '', 0, 'paolo alto', 'NO'),
(22, 'TOP 3 FRAMEWORKS OF PHP WHICH HELPS YOU GET JOB EASILY', 'EDUCATION', 'ENGLISH', 'laravel.jpg', '<p>There is no doubt that PHP is one of the best things happens to web development. Almost 80% of the websites in the world run on PHP. As the technology is evolving &nbsp;PHP is &nbsp;also upgrading to its frameworks.which are undoubtedly ruling the web industries&nbsp;</p><p>1: <strong>Laravel</strong>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;Laravel was created by Taylor Otwell. is a powerful MVC PHP framework, designed for developers who need a simple and elegant toolkit to create full-featured web applications.</p><p>It is a free, open-source web framework, &nbsp;for the development of web applications following the <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Model%E2%80%93view%E2%80%93controller" title="Modelâ€“viewâ€“controller">model&ndash;view&ndash;controller</a> (MVC) architectural pattern. Laravel&#39;s first beta release was made available on June 9, 2011, followed by the Laravel 1 release later in the same month. Laravel 1 included built-in support for authentication, <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Language_localisation" title="Language localisation">localization</a>, <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Model_(MVC)" title="Model (MVC)">models</a>, <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/View_(MVC)" title="View (MVC)">views</a>, <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Session_(computer_science)" title="Session (computer science)">sessions</a>, routing and other mechanisms, but lacked support for controllers that prevented it from being a true MVC framework. Laravel 2 was released in September 2011, bringing various improvements from the author and community. Major new features included the support for controllers, which made Laravel 2 a fully MVC-compliant framework, built-in support for the inversion of control ( principle, and a templating system called <em>Blade</em>. As a downside, support for third-party packages was removed in Laravel 2.Latest version on<strong>&nbsp;Laravel</strong> is 5.8 which was released on 26 February 2019</p>', 'phalcon-3.png', '<p>2:<strong>PHALCON</strong></p><p><strong>Phalcon</strong> is also &nbsp;based on the model&ndash;view&ndash;controller (MVC) pattern. Originally released in 2012, it is an open-source framework licensed under the terms of the BSD License. Unlike most PHP frameworks, Phalcon is implemented as a <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Web_server" title="Web server">web server</a> extension written in Zephir and <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/C_(programming_language)" title="C (programming language)">C</a>, aiming to boost execution speed, reduce resource usage, and handle more HTTP requests per second than comparable frameworks written primarily in PHP. Phalcon was created by Andr&eacute;s Guti&eacute;rrez .The framework was released with the name of<strong>&nbsp;spark</strong> in 2011 later changed to Phalcon,.</p><p>latest version is Phalcon 3.0.0 was released on 29 July 2016 </p>', 'symfony-logo.png', '<p>3: <strong>Symfony</strong>&nbsp;</p><p>Symfony was published as free software on October 18, 2005, and released under the MIT license. Symfony aims to speed up the creation and maintenance of web applications and to replace repetitive coding tasks.and has a low-performance overhead used with a bytecode cache. Symfony is aimed at building robust applications in an enterprise context, and aims to give developers full control over the configuration: from the directory structure to the foreign libraries, almost everything can be customized. To match enterprise development guidelines, Symfony is bundled with additional tools to help developers test, debug and document projects</p><p>latest version of Symfony is 4.2 which was released in July 2019</p>', 'Education', '2019-07-11 14:48:58', '', 0, 0, '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 0, 'Banglore', 'NO'),
